text: Šupljak (, ) is a village in Serbia. It is situated in the Subotica municipality, in the North Bačka District, Vojvodina province. The village has a Hungarian ethnic majority and its population numbering 1,310 people (2002 census). ==External links== * History of Šupljak ==See also== *List of places in Serbia *List of cities, towns and villages in Vojvodina Category:Places in Bačka Category:Subotica Category:Hungarian communities in Serbia
